<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10097861>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Elytroleptus luteus, a) head, anterior view, b) head, lateral view, c) antenna, d) right mandible, ventral view, e) labrum, f) right mandible, dorsal view, g) labium, dorsal view, h) left maxilla, ventral view, i) left maxilla, dorsal view, j) labium, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm for a, b, and c. Scale bars = 0.25 mm for d, e, f, g, h, i, and j." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10097861/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10097863>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Elytroleptus luteus, a) female, sternite VIII with brush, b) female, tergite VIII, c) female, ovipositor. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10097863/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10097867>
    dc:description "FIGURES 19–20. 19a) Character 1, State 0, genal length less than width, 19b) Character 1, State 1, genal length equal to width; 20a) Character 3, State 1, ultimate antennomere slightly appendiculate, 20b) Character 3, State 2, ultimate antennomere" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10097867/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10097871>
    dc:description "FIGURES 25–28. 25a) Character 2, State 0, antennal length in males reaching to less than half elytral length, 25b) Character 2, State 1, antennal length in males reaching to more than half elytral length, but not past elytral apices; 26a) Character 4, State 0, pronotal pubescence only with thin pubescence, 26b) Character 4, State 1, pronotal pubescence with thin pubescence and lines" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10097871/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

